                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/519: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the American Representation on the Preparatory
                        Commission</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-04-26T21:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1927—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 26—7:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>260. Preparatory Commission adjourned this evening. In closing speech President
                    singled out American delegation alone for warm tribute to our helpful attitude
                    which had promoted good understanding. He alluded to the forthcoming three-power
                    conversations as calculated to facilitate the further approach to the problem of
                    disarmanent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
